.IX Title "KAREMOTE 1"
.TH KAREMOTE 1 "2008-02-05" "perl v5.8.8" "Kadeploy commands"
.SH "NAME"
karemote \- issue a remote command as root on the deployed nodes.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
\&\fBkaremote\fR  [\fB\-m|\-\-machine\fR hostname] [\fB\-f\fR nodefile] [\fB\-c|\-\-command\fR \*(L"remote command\*(R"] [\fB\-v|\-\-verbose\fR]
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
karemote can be seen as a \fBfrontend to ease the creation of user's scripts\fR to ease experiments configuration on a set of deployed nodes.
.PP
Karemote is used in kaaddkeys.
.PP
This command is used to run a remote command as root on a set of deployed nodes.
The target nodes should be deployed on an user's authorized partition to ensure proper execution of the command.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.IX Header "OPTIONS"
.IP "\fB\-m|\-\-machine\fR hostname" 4
.IX Item "-m|--machine hostname"
Specifies a target host. This option can be used more than once to specify several target hosts.
.IP "\fB\-f\fR nodefile" 4
.IX Item "-f nodefile"
Specifies a file containing a set of target nodes.
.ie n .IP "\fB\-c\fR ""remote command""" 4
.el .IP "\fB\-c\fR ``remote command''" 4
.IX Item "-c remote command"
Specifies a command to run on target nodes as root.
.IP "\fB\-v, \-\-verbose\fR" 4
.IX Item "-v, --verbose"
verbose mode.
.SH "EXAMPLE"
.IX Header "EXAMPLE"
Echo coucou as root on all the nodes:
.ie n .IP "karemote \-f $OAR_NODEFILE \-c ""echo coucou""" 4
.el .IP "karemote \-f \f(CW$OAR_NODEFILE\fR \-c ``echo coucou''" 4
.IX Item "karemote -f $OAR_NODEFILE -c echo coucou"
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.IX Header "SEE ALSO"
\&\fIkaaddkeys\fR\|(1)
